glosses: To come alive, to come to life.
To gain strength and become lively.
(for a plant) To turn green from a withered state.
To become valid or active once again.

etymology:
Inherited from Ottoman Turkish دیرلمك (dirilmek), from دیری (diri), equivalent to
diri (“alive, living; lively”) + -l (verb-forming suffix) + -mek.
